How we share your Personal Data
We may share your Personal Data as follows:
Recipients
Why we share your Personal Data with these recipients
How these recipients will use your Personal Data
Other SMG companies.
Your Personal Data may be shared with, or accessed by, our affiliates who perform certain services for the rest of the SMG group (such as data hosting and marketing) or to coordinate our international strategy.
These recipients will use your Personal Data as described in this Privacy Notice.
The lawful basis we rely on for sharing your Personal Data with these recipients is that it is necessary for our and our group companies’ legitimate interests, namely coordinating intragroup services and group-wide strategy.
Service providers
We will share your Personal Data with companies that provide services to us, such as:
– Analytics service providers;
– Communications service providers, such as email distribution and optimization platforms;
– Data hosting, storage and security providers.
These recipients will use your Personal Data as processors on our instructions.
Buyers of our business
We may share Personal Data with other parties in connection with a transaction or potential transaction where we merge with another organization, file for bankruptcy, or sell some or all of our assets or stock. For instance, if we sell the Site to a third party, we will share the Personal Data we have collected through the Site with that buyer.
These recipients will use your Personal Data to complete a transaction to buy all or the part of our business that includes the Site. The lawful basis rely on for sharing Personal Data with these recipients is that it is necessary for our and the recipient’s legitimate interests, namely completing a transaction to buy all or part of our business.
Law enforcement, regulators and other parties for legal reasons
We may share your Personal Data with third parties as required by law or if we reasonably believe that such action is necessary to (i) comply with the law and the reasonable requests of law enforcement; (ii) detect and investigate illegal activities and breaches of agreements; and/or (iii) exercise or protect the rights, property, or personal safety of SMG, its users or others.
These recipients will use your Personal Data in the performance of their regulatory or law enforcement role. The lawful basis we rely on for sharing Personal Data with these recipients is that the processing is either necessary to comply with a legal obligation to which we are subject, or is necessary for our legitimate interests, namely enforcing our rights or complying with requests from regulatory authorities.
Cross-Border Transfers of Personal Data
SMG controls and operates the Site from the United States, and your Personal Data will primarily be processed by us and our service providers in the United States. It may also be accessed by our affiliates in the United Kingdom and Japan.
Any transfers of your Personal Data to a recipient outside the United Kingdom or European Economic Area will be made pursuant to appropriate safeguards in accordance with applicable law:
W
here we may transfer your Personal Data
Safeguards that apply to that transfer
United States
The transfer is subject to standard contractual clauses approved by the European Commission or the UK Information Commissioner for the transfer of Personal Data, or, for European residents, is to a company certified to the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework.
Japan
If you are in the EEA, the country is deemed to provide adequate protection for Personal Data by the European Commission. If you are in the UK, the country is deemed to provide adequate protection for Personal Data under the UK Data Protection Act 2018.
United Kingdom
The country is deemed by the European Commission
to provide adequate protection for Personal Data.
Your rights
If you are located in France, in addition to the rights set out in the “Your Rights” section of Part 1 of this Privacy Notice, you have the right to provide instructions regarding the retention, deletion and disclosure of your Personal Data after your death. In the absence of instructions from you, your successors may request the disclosure or deletion of your Personal Data by contacting us using the contact details in the “Who we are and how to contact us” section of this Privacy Notice above.
Your right to complain
If you reside in the UK, you have the right to make a complaint at any time to the Information Commissioner’s Office (“ICO”), the UK regulator for data protection issues. You can make a complaint via the ICO’s website (https://ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint/). This website also provides additional contact details for the ICO.
If you are resident in the EEA, you have the right to make a complaint at any time to the regulator in your jurisdiction. To find out how to contact your local regulator, please visit https://edpb.europa.eu/about-edpb/about-edpb/members_en.
